# Tailwind CSS & shadcn/ui Rules

- **Utility First**: Write styles exclusively using Tailwind CSS utility classes. Avoid writing custom CSS in separate files.
- **shadcn/ui Usage**: Before building common primitives (Buttons, Dialogs, Selects, Inputs), verify if they exist in `src/components/ui/`. Use them as basic building blocks.
- **Iconography**: Strictly use `lucide-react` for all icons. Keep sizes consistent using responsive classes (e.g., `className="w-4 h-4"`).
- **Layouts**: Prefer CSS Grid (`grid grid-cols-...`) and Flexbox (`flex flex-row...`) utilities. Avoid deprecated or legacy layout techniques.
